(140, 'P', 0, 'Stop "multitasking." Context switching is the fastest way to turn a 160 IQ into a 60 IQ.', 'Focus preservation'),
(141, 'P', 1, 'A deadline is a constraint, not a reason to commit crimes against the codebase.', 'Integrity under pressure'),
(142, 'P', 1, 'Technical debt is fine, as long as you have a repayment plan. Don’t let your project go bankrupt.', 'Debt management'),
(143, 'P', 2, 'Standardization is what allows teams to scale. Don’t be a "code rebel" just for the sake of your ego.', 'Team alignment'),
(144, 'P', 2, 'The best process is the one that disappears when you’re in the zone.', 'Invisible process'),
(145, 'E', 0, 'If you have to do it more than twice, script it. Your time is too expensive for repetitive motion.', 'Automation rule'),
(146, 'E', 0, 'Keyboard shortcuts are a high-yield investment. Seconds saved today are hours gained this year.', 'Micro-efficiency'),
(147, 'E', 1, 'Don’t watch the progress bar. Use that time to think about the next three steps.', 'Pipelining thoughts'),
(148, 'E', 1, 'A clean workspace (and a clean IDE) leads to a clean execution. Clear the clutter.', 'Environmental efficiency'),
(149, 'E', 2, 'Efficiency is doing the right thing, not just doing things fast. Don’t optimize a feature that shouldn’t exist.', 'Macro-efficiency'),
