(162, 'F', 2, 'Listen to your telemetry. The users will never tell you the truth, but the logs never lie.', 'Data-driven feedback'),
(163, 'L', 0, 'Hard-coding is just a loan you’re taking out against your future time. The interest rate is 100%.', 'Anti-hardcoding'),
(164, 'L', 0, 'If your logic feels like a "hack," it is a hack. Don''t ship it until you’ve found the "why."', 'Integrity in logic'),
(165, 'L', 1, 'State management is the art of knowing who to blame when things go wrong. Keep it centralized and predictable.', 'State logic'),
