(167, 'L', 2, 'The goal is not to write code that works; it’s to write code that’s impossible to use incorrectly.', 'Defensive design'),
(168, 'L', 2, 'Logic is the skeleton of the product. If the skeleton is deformed, no amount of UI makeup can save it.', 'Structural priority'),
(169, 'P', 0, 'A "Quick Fix" is the most permanent thing in software. If you don''t fix it right now, you never will.', 'Permanence of temporary fixes'),
(170, 'P', 0, 'Sleep on it. The solution you can''t find in 5 hours at night will often appear in 5 minutes in the morning.', 'Incubation effect'),
(171, 'P', 1, 'Tests aren''t a chore; they are a safety net that allows you to move at 200mph without fear.', 'Test-driven velocity'),
(172, 'P', 1, 'If it''s not in version control, it doesn''t exist. If it''s not backed up, it''s already gone.', 'Data survival'),
(173, 'P', 2, 'The best tool is the one that fits your brain, not the one that''s currently trending on Hacker News.', 'Tool pragmatism'),
